@startuml signals-detect-sequence
title Signal detection — call sequence\nPOST /api/v1/signals/detect

skinparam backgroundColor #FCFCFD
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 8
skinparam ArrowColor #455A64
skinparam ArrowFontColor #37474F
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #CFD8DC
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBackgroundColor #F4F6F8
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF8E1
skinparam noteBorderColor #E0C46C
skinparam participant {
  BorderColor #546E7A
  FontColor #FFFFFF
  FontStyle bold
}

actor "Client / cURL" as C #607D8B
participant "SignalResource\n+ Access-log filter" as API #4C78A8
participant "SignalService\n(@Transactional)" as SS #8E6FB0
participant "SignalDetectionService\nPURE CODE — no LLM" as SD #5AA469
participant "Trade / Signal\nrepositories" as REPO #C0566B
database "PostgreSQL" as DB #43A047

C -> API: POST /api/v1/signals/detect
activate API
note right of API #ECEFF1: log: API REQUEST →

API -> SS: detectAndPersist()
activate SS
SS -> REPO: trades disclosed in last 45 days
REPO -> DB: SELECT trades
DB -->> SS: trades

SS -> SD: detectAll(trades)
activate SD
note right of SD #ECEFF1
  Deterministic rules (no DB, no LLM):
  CLUSTER · OUTLIER ·
  LATE_DISCLOSURE · SECTOR_CONCENTRATION
end note
SD -->> SS: signals
deactivate SD

SS -> REPO: deleteAll() then persist(signals)
REPO -> DB: DELETE signals; INSERT signals
SS -->> API: persisted signals
deactivate SS

API -> API: map → SignalDto
API -->> C: 200 application/json
note right of API #ECEFF1: log: API RESPONSE ← 200
deactivate API

note across #FFFDE7
  Signals are produced entirely by deterministic code.
  The LLM never produces a signal — it only narrates them in the digest.
end note
@enduml
